subSubSection.paragraph:
Ðỗ 
et al.
(
2010
) reported 

P. fulvus

from the Xuan Son National Park (Phu Tho Province, 
Vietnam
). We received photos of three specimens from Dr. Đỗ Văn Nhượng. Those specimens are similar to the North Vietnamese shells in terms of shell shape and rib density, but have much thicker peristome and the ribbing on the last quarter of whorl is more widely-spaced than on the preceding areas.

Distribution (
Fig. 11
): The species inhabits a large geographic area of over 1300 km from Northern Vietnam (Ninh Binh Province) until the Chinese Chongqing and Hubei Provinces.
